msgid ""
"The Linux kernel assigns interface names with a specific prefix depending on "
"the type. Traditionally, all **Ethernet** interfaces, for example, began "
"with **eth**. The prefix was followed by a number, the first being 0 (eth0, "
"eth1, eth2...). The wifi interfaces were given a wlan prefix."
