#, no-wrap
msgid "The hostname"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:172
msgid "The `hostname` command displays or sets the host name of the system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "hostname [-f] [hostname]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:181
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"|  Option  |  Description                   |\n"
"|----------|--------------------------------|\n"
"| `-f`     | Display the FQDN               |\n"
"| `-i`     | Display the system IPs address |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:183
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:204
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:226
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:265
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:342
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:487
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:590
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:682
msgid "!!! Tip"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "    This command is used by various network programs to identify the machine.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:187
msgid ""
"To assign a host name, it is possible to use the `hostname` command, but the "
"changes will not be retained at the next boot. The command with no arguments "
"displays the host name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:189
msgid ""
"To set the host name, the file `/etc/sysconfig/network` must be modified:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:190
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"NETWORKING=yes\n"
"HOSTNAME=pc-rocky.mondomaine.lan\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:196
msgid ""
"The RedHat boot script also consults the `/etc/hosts` file to resolve the "
"host name of the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:198
msgid ""
"When the system boots, Linux evaluates the `HOSTNAME` value in the `/etc/"
"sysconfig/network` file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:200
msgid ""
"It then uses the `/etc/hosts` file to evaluate the main IP address of the "
"server and its host name. It deduces the DNS domain name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:202
msgid ""
"It is therefore essential to fill in these two files before any "
"configuration of network services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:206
#, no-wrap
msgid "    To know if this configuration is well done, the commands `hostname` and `hostname -f` must answer with the expected values.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:207
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/hosts file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:210
msgid ""
"The `/etc/hosts` file is a static host name mapping table, which follows the "
"following format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:211
#, no-wrap
msgid "@IP <hostname>  [alias]  [# comment]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:216
msgid "Example of `/etc/hosts` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:217
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"127.0.0.1       localhost localhost.localdomain\n"
"::1             localhost localhost.localdomain\n"
"192.168.1.10    rockstar.rockylinux.lan rockstar\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:224
msgid ""
"The `/etc/hosts` file is still used by the system, especially at boot time "
"when the system FQDN is determined."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:228
#, no-wrap
msgid "    RedHat recommends that at least one line containing the system name be filled in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:230
msgid ""
"If the **DNS** service (**D**omain **N**ame **S**ervice) is not in place, "
"you must fill in all the names in the hosts file for each of your machines."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:232
msgid ""
"The `/etc/hosts` file contains one line per entry, with the IP address, the "
"FQDN, then the host name (in that order) and a series of aliases (alias1 "
"alias2 ...). The alias is an option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:233
#, no-wrap
msgid "`/etc/nsswitch.conf` file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:236
msgid ""
"The **NSS** (**N**ame **S**ervice **S**witch) allows configuration files (e."
"g., `/etc/passwd`, `/etc/group`, `/etc/hosts`) to be substituted for one or "
"more centralized databases."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:238
msgid ""
"The `/etc/nsswitch.conf` file is used to configure the name service "
"databases."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"passwd: files\n"
"shadow: files\n"
"group: files\n"
"\n"
"hosts: files dns\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:248
msgid ""
"In this case, Linux will first look for a host name match (`hosts:` line) in "
"the `/etc/hosts` file (`files` value) before querying DNS (`dns` value)! "
"This behavior can simply be changed by editing the `/etc/nsswitch.conf` file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:250
msgid ""
"Of course, it is possible to imagine querying an LDAP, MySQL or other server "
"by configuring the name service to respond to system requests for hosts, "
"users, groups, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:252
msgid ""
"The resolution of the name service can be tested with the `getent` command "
"that we will see later in this course."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:253
#, no-wrap
msgid "`/etc/resolv.conf` file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:256
msgid ""
"The `/etc/resolv.conf` file contains the DNS name resolution configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:257
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#Generated by NetworkManager\n"
"domain mondomaine.lan\n"
"search mondomaine.lan\n"
"nameserver 192.168.1.254\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:267
#, no-wrap
msgid "    This file is historical. It is no longer filled in directly!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:269
msgid ""
"Newer generations of distributions have generally integrated the "
